
[1]shoeinghorn

   SHOEING'HORN, n. [shoe and horn.]

   1. A horn used to facilitate the entrance of the foot onto a narrow
   shoe.

   2. Any thing by which transaction is facilitated; any thing used as a
   medium; in contempt. [I have never heard this word in America.]
